dataIdInfo.idPurp: Range fans are polygon map features that represent rocket debris impact areas.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: This geospatial feature class consists of polygon geometry generated using Lat, Lon coordinates obtained from the UAF-GI Poker Flat Research Rocket Range impact areas (effective July 20, 1995) identifing polygon corners. Range fan polygons are map feature that represent rocket debris impact areas.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: University of Alaska Fairbanks - Geophysical Institute - Poker Flat Research Rocket Range, and UAF - GI - Geographic Information Network of Alaska (GINA).

prcStep.stepDesc:
Coordinates in Latitude and Longitude were provided on an inset to a print map in pdf format titled Poker Flat Research Range Flight Zones and Impact Areas (Effective: July 20, 1995) from Poker Flat Research Range to GINA. Coordinates were extracted into a table that was added to ArcMap. The Add X, Y Data command in ArcMap was performed on the table of coordinates to generate a point event layer which was exported as a shapefile.
Corner point shapefile was projected into Alaska Albers Equal Area Conic - NAD83 (EPSG:3338). Points were used as snap elements during generation of the polygons found in this feature class. Data editing was performed in ArcGIS Pro 1.4.
Features were attributed as per labels on the print map mentioned above.
